{"title_page": "Poul Richard H\u00f8j Jensen", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               =  Poul Richard H\u00f8j Jensen\n| image              =  Poul Richard H\u00f8j Jensen 2018.png\n| caption            =  \n| birth_name         =  Poul Richard H\u00f8j Jensen\n| birth_date         =  {{birth date and age|1944|06|02|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Copenhagen]], [[Denmark]]\n| death_date         =  <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1944|06|02|df=y}} -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| resting_place      = \n| resting_place_coordinates =  <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| burial_place       =  <!-- may be used instead of resting_place and resting_place_coordinates (displays \"Burial place\" as label) -->\n| burial_coordinates =  <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| monuments          = \n| residence          =  Alternating in [[Burnham on Crouch]] and [[Freetown, Antigua and Barbuda]]\n| nationality        = [[Demographics of Denmark|Dane]]\n| citizenship        =  \n| education          =  \n| alma_mater         =  \n| occupation         =  Retired\n*Sailmaker\n*Boatbuilder\n| years_active       =  \n| employer           =  \n| known_for          =  (Olympic) [[yachtsman]], Sailmaker & Boatbuilder. PRHJ won more than 125 major yachting titles. This includes Olympic, International and national championships in different sailing classes. \n| notable_works      =  \n| home_town          =  \n| height             =  {{convert|1.83|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| weight             =  \n| title              =  \n| term               =  \n| predecessor        =  \n| successor          =  \n| spouse             =  Birthe Rasmussen<br>Sophia\n| children           =  Pia, Claus, Adrian and Justin (the latter two step) <BR>'''Grandchildren:''' Mie, Mathias, Bella, Rommey, Harry, Tom and Rosie.\n| mother             =  <!-- may be used (optionally with mother parameter) i